# API proxy — same-origin axios baseURL `/api/v1` works in prod by routing
# `/api/*` to the Render backend. Must come before the SPA fallback below.
/api/*  https://lms-development.onrender.com/api/:splat  200!

# Netlify SPA fallback — React Router owns client-side routing, so every
# unmatched path serves index.html and lets the router resolve it. Without
# this, refreshing /app/foo on a Netlify deploy would 404.
/*    /index.html   200
